we're very powerful in exp groups, can solo very well, and desired on raids. there is some debate over whether summoning mod rods on raids should be lessened so we can nuke more, but other than that we mages dont have anything to complain about.<br>
<br>
judging from the new spell lists, unfortunately it looks like we soon will again.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #1)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: again, we get knocked a few pegs down the nuking totem pole. congrats enchanters on being the now 3rd class to outnuke mages in 1 or more respects.<br>
<br>
its completely breath taking and outrageous that they honestly think they can take any more relative nuking power from us than theyve already done.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #2)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: the vs summoned cc spells. unless absolutely every zone in pop has a good amount of summoned creatures to make up for the complete lack of them elsewhere, expect to see these in the back of your spellbooks.<br>
<br>
honestly, do they think this useless fluff is supposed to make up for druids ever increasing nuking power? is it supposed to compensate for the fact even ENCHANTERS are nuking better than us now? i say no way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #3)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: this is really more of a potential issue, a sign of things to come. if you notice, the levels we recieve our pets are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not in sync</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with the 50-60 progression.<br>
the old system was earth, fire, air, and finally the best offensive pet water. <br>
the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> new</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> list follows as air, water, fire, and earth!<br>
what does this mean?<br>
if i know how verant thinks our collective minds work, and i think i do, they are going to use this as an excuse to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not give our pets the proper upgrades they should recieve.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
think back. remember right before your water pet, you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> knew</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that next pet was going to be a damage dealing monster. it was the last in the set. it backstabbed and nuked. you couldnt WAIT to scribe it -- it was like wizards getting sunstrike/ice comet.<br>
<br>
you see, by making the water pet an earlier pet, they DONT need to make it incredibly powerful relative to other pets, since psychologically the player wont be expecting it. rather, they chose to put the most &quot;well rounded&quot; pet, earth, as the last pet in the set. even though a player expects the last pet to be powerful, they will only be expecting &quot;good tanking, good damage&quot;. a player expecting this will accept disappointment (in the form of a nerf) more easily.<br>
needless to say, a well rounded tankish pet is in general less useful than an offensively specilized pet (which is why it was the first pet in the old set).<br>
now, unless they plan on totally redistributing the abilities of our new pets (i doubt it), take this as a warning sign.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #4)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: if you notice, necros have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> three</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> pets from 60-65. thats as many as they got from all of 50-60. mages are only getting <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> four</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (one full set).<br>
mages are getting <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> half</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the pets we should (we should be getting 2 pets a level or more).<br>
<br>
why would they give us so few pets? the only reason i can think of, perhaps its because they dont plan on continuing the power gap we currently enjoy. i do strongly feel our position regarding pets is being threatened.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #5)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: no pet haste on test. all other major pet casters already have haste spells on test. when you consider 3, 4 and 5... well things do not look good.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #6)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: our ds. so i see druids not only will continue to outnuke us by an even larger margin, but their damage shield will equal ours too? actually, their ds is totally better when you consider how much more mana efficient it is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>issue #7)</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: so many lure spells on test (intresting enough, mages dont have any). perhaps the new &quot;short but challenging&quot; encounters will include high resist mobs mages cant nuke well at all? could this be the return of kunark?<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------<br>
after some short lived fun, more and more it looks like depressing times ahead for our class. i do hope they seriously listen to us and reconsider these new spells and environments.<br>
